Gathering some links for the benefit of people who want to check-in changes to vanilla Emacs.

* [https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#AssignCopyright  Why assign copyright]
* [https://www.gnu.org/prep/maintain/html_node/Copyright-Papers.html Copyright papers]
* [https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/gnulib.git/tree/doc/Copyright How the request forms look]
* [https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/emacs/Copyright-Assignment.html Copyright Assignment in Emacs Manual]
* [https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs.git/tree/CONTRIBUTE CONTRIBUTE] of Emacs distribution.
* [https://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2018-02/msg00002.html Assigning copyright for people under 18]:
: If the person is under 18 years old their parent needs to also sign
: the contract.  The biggest sticking point is that the assignment is
: only valid up until that person's 18th birthday.

Insistent of Assignment of rights is met with mixed reaction in general.

* [https://twit.tv/floss117 FLOSS weekly podcast] has some good reasons why getting the copyright registered is important and useful.

See also 

* EmacsSchism
* [https://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2013-03/msg00228.html Selective withholding of assignments] and a followup  [https://lwn.net/Articles/543339/ LWN article]


